Real Madrid have confirmed that the club has agreed on a transfer deal for Brazil midfielder, Reinier Jesus, to join Borussia Dortmund. Jesus, 18, will join Dortmund on a two-year-loan until June 30, 2020. Zinedine Zidane’s side made this in a statement on the club’s official website on Wednesday. The statement read: “Real Madrid CF and Borussia Dortmund have agreed to loan the player Reinier Jesus for the next two seasons, until June 30, 2022.” Reacting, Jesus said: “I am happy to be with BVB now. “The club is known for backing young players and making them better. “I want to learn a lot here, play a lot and help the team to be successful. I hope that we’ll have many happy moments together.”